The paper deals with coordinating behaviors of multi-robot systems, which falls under the scope of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the need for composing multiple behaviors, which involves decision-making and planning, making it relevant to multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The use of control barrier functions suggests a focus on control theory and optimization (cs.SY). The paper also mentions the use of communication and localization, which are important topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the case study involves testing on a robotic test-bed, which suggests a focus on machine learning and experimentation (cs.LG).
